.TH "_omap2_module_wait_ready" 9 "_omap2_module_wait_ready" "May 2021" "Kernel Hacker's Manual" LINUX
.SH NAME
_omap2_module_wait_ready \- wait for an OMAP module to leave IDLE
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B "void" _omap2_module_wait_ready
.BI "(struct clk_hw_omap *clk "  ");"
.SH ARGUMENTS
.IP "clk" 12
struct clk * belonging to the module
.SH "DESCRIPTION"
If the necessary clocks for the OMAP hardware IP block that
corresponds to clock \fIclk\fP are enabled, then wait for the module to
indicate readiness (i.e., to leave IDLE).  This code does not
belong in the clock code and will be moved in the medium term to
module-dependent code.  No return value.
